==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Appeach
<hw>Ap*peach"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>apechen</ets>, for <ets>empechen</ets>, OF. <ets>empeechier</ets>,
F. <ets>emp⟦ecir⟧cher</ets>, to hinder. See <er>Impeach</er>.]</ety>
<def>To impeach; to accuse; to asperse; to inform against; to
reproach.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And oft of error did himself <qex>appeach</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appeacher</ent>⟦br⟧
